page.title: 08BIRDS AROUND NORTH SCARLE
page.content: In North Scarle I have seen lots of blackbirds. They eat bread and fat. They drink milk and water. The blackbirds live in the trees near all the leaves. The other bird I've seen is the thrush.They eat fat and bread. They drink water and milk. At the top of our house there is a magpies nest and it has about five babies in it. They eat anything and drink anything. I have seen a sparrow up in our tree.They like to sing songs to one and other. They like to eat fat and bread and they drink water. We have a bird box in our garden and bluetits are in it and they have laid about six eggs.They keep going in and out the box.They eat bread and fat They drink water.The babies have flown away now. water.
